# Move master product between categories (2025-12-04 17:16Z)

_**User (2025-12-03 16:38Z)**_

when viewing the category manager (/admin/categories) it should be easy to move a master product from a sub-category (or category) to another one. This will results in moving all the specific products under that master product so open a confirmation popup modal dialog, show the affected items and confirm the move

```diff
      return { success: !error, data: result, error: error?.message };

+ 
+ export const moveMasterItem = async (masterItemId: string, targetCategoryId: string) =&gt; {
+     try {
+         const { error } = await supabaseAdmin
+             .from('master_items')
+             .update({ category_id: targetCategoryId })
+             .eq('id', masterItemId);
+             
+         if (error) throw error;
+         return { success: true };
+     } catch (e: any) {
+         return { success: false, message: e.message };
+     }
+ };
  
```

The "Runtime Error" regarding the failed chunk load was likely caused by a transient Hot Module Replacement (HMR) issue in Next.js when modifying both the server-side service (`categoryService.ts`) and the client-side page (`page.tsx`) simultaneously. I have triggered a rebuild, and the page is now loading correctly.

I have implemented the requested functionality:
1.  **Move Master Item**: Added a "Move" button (folder input icon) to each master item in the product list.
2.  **Modal Dialog**: Clicking the button opens a modal to select the destination category.
3.  **Confirmation**: The modal shows a warning that all specific products under the master item will be moved (since they inherit the category from the master item) and lists the affected products.
4.  **Backend Logic**: Added `moveMasterItem` server action to update the `category_id` of the master item.

The feature is now ready to use.

**Files updated:**
-   `src/lib/categoryService.ts`: Added `moveMasterItem` function.
-   `src/app/admin/categories/page.tsx`: Added "Move" button, modal state, and handler logic.
